        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 tests: Determine sanity-hsm memory leak",
        "message": "LU-0000 tests: Determine sanity-hsm memory leak\n\nIn review-zfs, sanity-hsm is failing with a memory leak. This patch\nis to determine what test is leaking memory.\n\nCurrently, 'complete $SECONDS' is called before\ncheck_and_cleanup_lustre which is where the memory leak/hang occurs.\nMove 'complete $SECONDS' after check_and_cleanup_lustre to see if\nthis will trigger a fail of the test suite.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly alwaysuploadlogs envdefinitions=SLOW=yes, mdtfilesystemtype=zfs mdsfilesystemtype=zfs ostfilesystemtype=zfs clientdistro=el6.6 ossdistro=el6.6 mdsdistro=el6.6 clientarch=x86_64 ossarch=x86_64 mdsarch=x86_64 testlist=sanity-hsm\n\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5d3704d33e99b78e41b636207a06a4c37a1d8038\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
